# Security rules — Meavo org standard

Org standard (see STANDARDS.md §4 in meavo-agent-templates). Deviations for this repo are listed at the bottom.

## Auth at every layer

- Verify auth independently in: middleware (pages), section layouts, Server Actions, and API routes.
- Middleware passes `/api/*` through — never assume an API route is protected.
- This repo's auth gates: `requireRpAccess()` in `src/lib/meavo-auth.ts` (pages/layouts), `requireActionSession()` / `requireApiSession()` in `src/lib/api/require-session.ts` (Server Actions / API routes).
- Tool card gating: check `ToolCardAccess` for `RP_TOOL_CARD_ID` (`seed-rp-tool`) at login AND on every authenticated request, so revocation in gateway Admin takes effect immediately. Never look up the card by `linkedAppKey` at runtime.
- Role routing on top of the tool-card gate: `src/lib/viewer-context.ts` + `src/lib/domain/authz.ts` decide per-persona permissions — enforce them in domain functions, not only in UI.

## Sessions & credentials

- NextAuth v5 JWT sessions; Google OAuth only, invite-only — the user must already exist in the shared gateway `User` table.
- Session user carries `id` via `src/types/next-auth.d.ts`.
- Admin simulation: `boyan@meavo.com` / `todor@meavo.com` may act as any `@meavo.com` user via the `rp_simulate_email` cookie — resolve the effective user through `resolveViewerContext`, never trust the cookie directly.

## Routes & rendering

- Cron routes: `CRON_SECRET` Bearer auth on every `/api/cron/*` handler via `isAuthorizedCronRequest` (`src/lib/cron-auth.ts`); automation source gating via `gateCronOrRun` (`src/lib/cron-gate.ts`).
- `export const dynamic = "force-dynamic"` on authenticated layouts and DB-touching pages.
- Never return stack traces to clients in production.

## Headers & content

- `next.config.ts` sets: `X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff`, `X-Frame-Options: DENY`, `Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin`, `Strict-Transport-Security`.
- Uploads (RP photos): Vercel Blob, Server Action body limit 10 MB, validate MIME + extension (`src/lib/domain/rp-photos.ts`).

## Secrets

- No secrets in client code, comments, or committed files.
- Document env var names in `.env.example` only — never values.

## Repo-specific deviations

- No Credentials provider: Google OAuth only, so bcrypt password rules and the shared `LoginThrottle` table are N/A here.
- Session is not extended with `systemRole` / `hrAccess` — roles are derived per-request from email via `viewer-context.ts` / `authz.ts`.
- `X-Frame-Options` is `DENY` (stricter than the org's `SAMEORIGIN`).
- Admin simulation cookie (`rp_simulate_email`) is an RP-specific pattern — do not copy into new apps.
